    "body": "I am trying to run a local instance of hardhat using a script. I am seeing lots of logs (like all the accounts that have the 10k ETH). I would prefer to hide all those logs when I boot up. Is this the same issue?\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nnode myScript.js\r\n```\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst hre = require('hardhat');\r\n\r\n(async function () {\r\n  hre.run('node');\r\n  await hre.network.provider.send('hardhat_setLoggingEnabled', [ false ]);\r\n})().catch(console.error);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `setLoggingEnabled` request seems to turn off the logs, but not initially, I am still seeing logs before that request gets processed. I have also tried `hre.run('node', { loggingEnabled: false });` but that doesn't seem to work at all. I also have that set in my config file but it gets ignored. I just want to confirm this is the same issue. If it is not, is there a way for me to turn off the logs? Thank you.",
